A housing construction project in Buffalo City Metro worth millions came to a standstill yesterday after angry people took to the streets and broke into unoccupied RDP houses. Residents from Ndancama informal settlement yesterday burnt tyres and piled rubble to protest against an unfair housing allocation process.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions